Large enterprises are poised to capture a significant market share in the ARA market due to their ability to invest in advanced automation technologies. These organizations have the resources and infrastructure to implement complex ARA solutions that can drive efficiency and agility in their software development processes. On the other hand, small and medium-sized enterprises (SMEs) are also recognizing the benefits of ARA tools in accelerating their release cycles and improving application quality. As SMEs continue to digitalize their operations, the demand for ARA solutions tailored to their specific needs is likely to increase.

In terms of verticals, the IT & telecom sector is expected to lead the market growth in the ARA segment. The rapid pace of innovation in the IT industry necessitates efficient release automation processes to meet customer demands and stay ahead of the competition. With the increasing complexity of software development projects, ARA solutions play a crucial role in enabling organizations to deliver software faster and with fewer errors. The healthcare, BFSI, retail, and manufacturing sectors are also witnessing a growing adoption of ARA tools to enhance their software delivery capabilities and improve overall operational efficiency.

